# SceneGraph XML Component Rules

## Component Structure

Every XML component must follow this structure order:

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<component name="MyComponent" extends="Group">
  <interface>
    <!-- public fields -->
  </interface>
  <script type="text/brightscript" uri="MyComponent.brs" />
  <children>
    <!-- child nodes -->
  </children>
</component>
```

- Always specify `extends` — typically `Group`, `Task`, `ContentNode`, or another custom component.
- Component filenames must match the component `name` attribute.
- Place all XML components under the `components/` directory.

## Interface Fields

- Declare all public fields in `<interface>` with explicit types and default values:

```xml
<!-- BAD: no type, no default -->
<field id="title" />

<!-- GOOD -->
<field id="title" type="string" value="" />
```

- Use `alias` to expose nested child fields to parent components instead of deep node traversal.
- Use `onChange` to bind observer callbacks directly in XML when appropriate.
- Valid field types: `string`, `integer`, `float`, `boolean`, `uri`, `node`, `array`, `assocarray`, `vector2d`, `color`, `time`, `nodearray`, `floatarray`, `intarray`.

## Children & Node IDs

- Give meaningful `id` attributes to nodes you need to reference from BrightScript via `findNode()`.
- Avoid unnecessary `id` attributes on decorative/static nodes.
- Use layout nodes (`LayoutGroup`, `Rectangle`, `Group`) to structure UI hierarchically.
- Set `translation`, `itemSize`, `itemSpacing` as arrays `[x, y]`, not strings — type mismatches cause silent failures.

## Script References

- Reference BrightScript files with relative `uri` paths from the component:

```xml
<script type="text/brightscript" uri="MyComponent.brs" />
```

- A component may include multiple `<script>` tags for shared utility scripts.
- Avoid inline `<script>` CDATA blocks in XML; keep logic in separate `.brs` files.

## Initialization Order

Understand and respect the initialization sequence:

1. `<children>` nodes are created with their XML-specified field values
2. `<interface>` fields are initialized with default or caller-specified values
3. `init()` is called in the associated BrightScript file

- Observers set in `init()` do NOT fire for initial field values. Call the handler explicitly in `init()` if needed.
- `getParent()` returns `invalid` inside `init()` — do not rely on parent context during initialization.

## Task Components

- Extend `Task` for all background/async work (network, file I/O, computation).
- Define `functionName` in the interface or set it in `init()` to specify the entry point.
- Control tasks via the `control` field: `"run"`, `"stop"`, `"done"`.
- Design task interfaces with clear input/output fields:

```xml
<interface>
  <field id="request" type="assocarray" />
  <field id="response" type="assocarray" />
</interface>
```

- Avoid accessing `m.top` or `m.global` heavily from within task threads — each access triggers a Rendezvous with the render thread.
- Use port-based `observeFieldScoped("field", m.port)` in task threads instead of callback-based observers.

## Focus Management

- Only one node can have focus at a time. Always call `setFocus(true)` on the intended node after screen transitions.
- Implement `onKeyEvent(key as String, press as Boolean) as Boolean` to handle remote key presses; return `true` if handled, `false` to propagate.
- Avoid focus loops — ensure back-navigation always has a clear target.
